<subSubSection id="C37E65015A729806F7F1FC4DE843FA16" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BDB368A5A729806F7F1FC4DE456FA39" blockId="5.[2054,2649,1006,1428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="B910EA985A729806F7F1FC4DE6A4FBA6" bold="true" box="[2054,2209,1006,1035]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C644D095A729806F745FC4DE64EFB9F" authority="Simonetta, 1968" authorityName="Simonetta" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Amblysomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tytonis">Amblysomus tytonis Simonetta, 1968</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B0C3CD75A729806F7ACFBB2E7D8FB05" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3804714314" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
Giohar, southern Somalia. Taxonomic placement of 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D095A729806F66CFB9FE7F4FBF4" authorityName="Simonetta" authorityYear="1968" box="[2459,2545,1084,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Amblysomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tytonis">tytonis</taxonomicName>
is uncertain (incertae sedis). It was previously assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D095A729806F6C5FB24E7DCFB05" authorityName="Pomel" authorityYear="1848" box="[2354,2521,1159,1192]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Amblysomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Amblysomus</taxonomicName>
,
</materialsCitation>
<taxonomicName id="4C644D095A729806F60DFB24E648FB7D" authorityName="Roberts" authorityYear="1924" class="Mammalia" family="Chrysochloridae" genus="Chlorotalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Chlorotalpa</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D095A729806F755FB10E744FB7D" authorityName="Mivart" authorityYear="1867" box="[2210,2369,1203,1232]" class="Mammalia" family="Chrysochloridae" genus="Calcochloris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Calcochloris</taxonomicName>
but here included in 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D095A729806F7C2FB75E697FB5A" box="[2101,2194,1238,1271]" class="Mammalia" family="Chrysochloridae" genus="Huetia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Huetia</taxonomicName>
because cladistic analyses of the few characteristics available suggest that it is more closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D095A729806F600FA8AE66BFAC0" baseAuthorityName="Huet" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Mammalia" family="Chrysochloridae" genus="Huetia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucorhina">H. leucorhina</taxonomicName>
. It is known only from a partially complete specimen in an owl pellet.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB368A5A729806FA55FA3DE843FA16" blockId="5.[1438,2646,1438,1979]" box="[1442,1606,1438,1467]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Monotypic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37E65015A729806FA56FA61E681F9A7" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" type="distribution">
<caption id="DF1B66025A729806FA56FA61E681F9A7" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6624516" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6624516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6624516/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" targetBox="[1439,2030,1012,1426]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8BDB368A5A729806FA56FA61E681F9A7" blockId="5.[1438,2646,1438,1979]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="B910EA985A729806FA56FA61E855FA4E" bold="true" box="[1441,1616,1474,1507]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from the type locality in S Somalia, with no subsequent records, although this might reflect a lack of sampling.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37E65015A729806FA56F9B2E838F9F5" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDB368A5A729806FA56F9B2E838F9F5" blockId="5.[1438,2646,1438,1979]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="B910EA985A729806FA56F9B2E89EF99F" bold="true" box="[1441,1691,1553,1586]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
There is no information available for this species, except the presence of M”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37E65015A729806FA56F9CBE7C4F92C" box="[1441,2497,1640,1665]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BDB368A5A729806FA56F9CBE7C4F92C" blockId="5.[1438,2646,1438,1979]" box="[1441,2497,1640,1665]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="B910EA985A729806FA56F9CBE80AF92C" bold="true" box="[1441,1551,1640,1665]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Habitat.</emphasis>
Dense bushland and thicket, and savanna of the Somali Peninsula.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37E65015A729806FA57F924E6B3F962" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph id="8BDB368A5A729806FA57F924E6B3F962" blockId="5.[1438,2646,1438,1979]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="B910EA985A729806FA57F924E8ADF905" bold="true" box="[1440,1704,1671,1704]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
There is no specific information available for this species, but the Somali Golden Mole is probably primarily insectivorous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37E65015A729806FA57F97AE910F95B" box="[1440,1813,1753,1782]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" type="breeding">
<paragraph id="8BDB368A5A729806FA57F97AE910F95B" blockId="5.[1438,2646,1438,1979]" box="[1440,1813,1753,1782]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="B910EA985A729806FA57F97AE823F95B" bold="true" box="[1440,1574,1753,1782]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Breeding.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37E65015A729806FA69F95EE97DF8B3" box="[1438,1912,1789,1822]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" type="activity">
<paragraph id="8BDB368A5A729806FA69F95EE97DF8B3" blockId="5.[1438,2646,1438,1979]" box="[1438,1912,1789,1822]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="B910EA985A729806FA69F95EE88FF8B3" bold="true" box="[1438,1674,1789,1822]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37E65015A729806FA57F887E74EF8E8" box="[1440,2379,1828,1861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BDB368A5A729806FA57F887E74EF8E8" blockId="5.[1438,2646,1438,1979]" box="[1440,2379,1828,1861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
